name: me to you
text:
I attended St Rose of Lima Catholic Church's 86th Lawn Festival and enjoyed the church.  It reminded me of what our church use to be before it was torn apart, turned around, and bricked.

I was looking forward to gumbo, and stuffed crab, but was disappointed in the lack of seasoning in either. The stuffed crab did not have any onion, celery, parsley, Italian Seasoning. The gumbo did not have any seasoning and was watery, more like gravy. It should have been put on a low heat and allowed to thicken. Everyone I knew loved it but me. I said, "It is not like Mama's.  No seasoning, and the gumbo's too runny."

I realize the necessity to cool it with the seasoning when selling to the public because of allergies.  One cousin said that he is allergic to black pepper. Most of the people who grew up in this parish are related.  It was my first visit and everyone was very nice.

I hope they are not offended by my review but it is what it is. The gumbo was too watery, and the stuffed crab lacked seasoning.

text: Newest Catholic parish in Archdiocese of Mobile meets in a borrowed warehouse in Spanish Fort, Alabama, Sunday 8:00am and 10:30am for Catholic Mass@ 9315 Spanish Fort Blvd (a.k.a.US31).  Both priests preach about Jesus and what He invites us to live for in Him and each other. Parish truly connects with Jesus in the Sacraments and each other. Sunday School between the Masses includes interesting topics for adults, while every youth class is on the same theme tied to the Lectionary. Children's Liturgy for the bitsy ones occurs while Mom and Dad hear a top notch homily. Kids love the doughnuts after Mass; parents love the coffee. BRING A SWEATER! The  A/C has to run even during the winter to prevent humidity from making the floors sweat!  Want to see the future building site? Head due east on US 31 approx 3 miles corner of US 31 @ Stroh Rd. across from Shambo Rd.

You should not bring in cell phones, leave them in your car. The greeters outside the sanctuary are just as bad. I have not been to mass in a few months because I have become so discouraged. This is the Lords house, do you not remember how angry Christ was when he found the money changers were just on the steps of the synagogue?. The church is to be honored and respected.You are also disrespecting our priest Father Roy, the people in the church and you shame youreslf.

The Catholic church is universal and although it was said in Korean it was easy to follow along due the to traditions of the mass and the readings being the same worldwide each Sunday.  It happened to be Parents' Day in Korea (traditional Mother's day for the USA coincidentally) so the children sang and brought all parents flowers! Thank you to everyone for their open arms and kindness.  God Bless this growing church!
